RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 18000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PAT'S PALACE dueled with an inner rival into the first turn and down the early backstretch, then gradually inched away at the three eighths marker to lead the way into the far turn and kept clear down the stretch to prevail. ZIPSY ROSE LEE was rated while three wide in the middle of the field down the backstretch, then steadily urged throughout the far turn, rallied in the late stretch but could not catch the leader in the end. DISHIN' IT OUT tracked the pace from the inside throughout the backstretch, then kept on under a strong drive on the far turn and was able to hold the show position in the end. EMERSON'S DREAM chased the pace while two wide down the backstretch and into the turn, rallied in the upper stretch but showed little effort in the end. PRETTY HEART dueled from the inside into the first turn and down the backstretch, then flattened out on the far turn and had no final bid in the end. MYSTERIOUSJUSTICE raced in the three path at an even pace throughout and was no threat. EXPLOSIVE SKIES was unhurried early, then settled along the inside, made a mild bid on the far turn and was no menace. GET STORM AWAY settled at the back of the pack and was no factor. PADDI'S WISH stumbled at the start and lost rider. There was an INQUIRY in regards to the start of the race. After review, the STEWARDS took no action.
